CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 26, 1946, pg. 17, reads: "Rent Control Debate - Fr. Charles O. Rice, director of the Rent Control Division of the OPA, and Alfred N. Murrer, president of the Pennsylvania Real Estate Board, debated the issues involved in price control of rent ceilings, at the YMCA Wednesday Luncheon Forum. The debate will be continued over KDKA Sunday, Jan. 27, 4:30 to 5 P. M. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Alfred N. Murrer speaking behind table, with Father Charles Owen Rice on left, and another man on right, in Centre Avenue YMCA with Henry O. Tanner painting "Christ and His Mother" in background
